# CIA Triad
## Description
Security Professionals evaluate threats based on the potential impact they have on the Confidentiality, Integrity and Availablity of an organisations assets

## Confidentiality
Refers to a companies efforts to keep data private.
It's about controlling access to data and unathourised disclosure.
Only those authorised to certain data are allowed access and those who aren't allowed are prevented.

## Integrity
Ensures data is untampered and can therefore be trusted.
data must be correct, authentic and reliable.
Countermeasures used for integrity might include: Encryption, Hashing, IDS etc

## Availability
Data must be readily availble at any time to any authorised users.
Networks and systems are up and running correctly
